{"ts": "2026-06-07T23:06:35.557767+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "I can see there are exactly three migration files in the `migrations/` directory, numbered sequentially. Here's the complete migration history in application order:\n\n---\n\n## Migration 1: `001_create_users.sql`\n\n**Creates the `users` table** with these columns:\n\n| Column | Type | Constraints |\n|---|---|---|\n| `id` | `BIGSERIAL` | `PRIMARY KEY` (auto-incrementing) |\n| `email` | `TEXT` | `UNIQUE NOT NULL` |\n| `display_name` | `TEXT` | *(nullable)* |\n| `created_at` | `TIMESTAMPTZ` | `NOT NULL DEFAULT now()` |\n\nThis is the foundational table — every user gets a surrogate numeric ID and a unique email. The `display_name` is optional.\n\n---\n\n## Migration 2: `002_create_sessions.sql`\n\n**Creates the `sessions` table** with these columns:\n\n| Column | Type | Constraints |\n|---|---|---|\n| `id` | `UUID` | `PRIMARY KEY` |\n| `user_id` | `BIGINT` | `NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE` |\n| `issued_at` | `TIMESTAMPTZ` | `NOT NULL DEFAULT now()` |\n| `expires_at` | `TIMESTAMPTZ` | `NOT NULL` |\n\nThis ties a session to a user via a foreign key. The `ON DELETE CASCADE` means if a user is deleted, all their sessions are automatically cleaned up. Session IDs use UUIDs rather than the auto-incrementing serial used for users.\n\n---\n\n## Migration 3: `003_add_session_index.sql`\n\n**Adds a performance index** on the `sessions` table:\n\n```sql\nCREATE INDEX idx_sessions_user_id ON sessions(user_id);\n```\n\nThis speeds up the most common query pattern — \"look up all sessions for a given user\" — which is otherwise a sequential scan on a foreign key column with no index of its own.\n\n---\n\n**In summary:** The schema models a simple auth system — users have sessions. The three migrations follow a clean progression: (1) establish the core entity, (2) create the dependent entity with a foreign key, (3) add an index for query performance. No down/rollback migrations are present; these are forward-only SQL files.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 774, "prompt_tokens": 6009, "total_tokens": 6783, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 282, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 5504, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0003028312, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 8.61112e-05, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00021672}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780873585-4NQbfH0b3HagfW4SjvDl", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea456-62c6-7243-9ced-973830f9b176-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 6009, "output_tokens": 774, "total_tokens": 6783, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 5504}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 282}}}}]}}}
